All learner-developed source code is released under the MIT license, so if you want or need to your application to be running after Labs, you can fork the repository and deploy to the infrastructure of your choosing.</span></span>

<span key="98d5bb25281b4d938cf8e1912792d26b"><span offset-key="98d5bb25281b4d938cf8e1912792d26b:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">â€‹</span></span></span><a href="https://www.notion.so/Design-Critiques-b472f5cb8c5445e2adf558b888a85906" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="32cfe5c3d77244ac9a815a993e274e6b" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-74619_259-74620-237__"><span data-key="55e20756f6184b1ab6b80f7686380384"><span data-offset-key="55e20756f6184b1ab6b80f7686380384:0">Design Critiques</span></span></span></a><span key="20fb958bfad146488c3d71eaf66e2e89"><span offset-key="20fb958bfad146488c3d71eaf66e2e89:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">â€‹</span></span></span>

<span key="d28d03d212554425ab512bc13daffa63"><span offset-key="d28d03d212554425ab512bc13daffa63:0">Design Leads meet with the Design Manager at least once per sprint to present design planning for group discussion.</span></span>
